## Jig Integration

### How Skills Load

AGENTS.md is loaded as system context at session start. Jig skills are
markdown files that the agent reads on demand when referenced by path.

**To activate a Jig skill**, read its SKILL.md file and follow the
instructions within:
```
Read the file at <path-to-skill/SKILL.md> and follow its instructions.
```

**Tier behavior in Codex:**

| Jig Tier | AGENTS.md Equivalent |
|----------|---------------------|
| Standards (`alwaysApply: true`) | Inlined in AGENTS.md (always in context) |
| Domain (globs) | Read on demand when working on matching files |
| Feature (narrow globs) | Read on demand when working on matching features |
| Workflow (explicit) | Read on user request (e.g., "run the kickoff workflow") |

### Skill Locations

Jig discovers skills from three directories in priority order:

```
1. team/skills/         <- Highest priority (team overrides)
2. packs/*/skills/      <- Pack defaults (e.g., packs/engineering/skills/)
3. core/skills/         <- Framework defaults
```

If the same skill name exists in multiple locations, the highest-priority
version wins. Team skills override pack skills override core skills.

### Tool Name Mapping

Jig skills reference tools by their Claude Code names. When executing in
Codex, use these equivalents:

| Jig / Claude Code Tool | Codex Equivalent |
|------------------------|------------------|
| `Read` | `file_read` |
| `Edit` | `file_edit` |
| `Write` | `file_write` |
| `Grep` | `grep_search` |
| `Glob` | `file_search` |
| `Bash` | `shell` |
| `Task` (subagent) | Sequential execution (no native subagent support) |
| `Skill` (invoke) | Read the skill file directly |

**Note:** Jig skills that use `Task` for parallel subagent execution
(e.g., `jig-team-dev`) require sequential fallback in Codex. Execute
tasks one at a time rather than spawning parallel agents.

### Configuration

`casaflow.config.md` in the project root configures the pipeline, review swarm,
branching, and commit conventions. Skills read it directly as markdown
context. No adapter translation is needed for configuration.

### Starting Work

To begin the Jig pipeline in Codex:

1. Read `casaflow.config.md` for pipeline configuration
2. Read `core/skills/jig-kickoff/SKILL.md` and follow its instructions
3. Follow the pipeline stages as directed by the skill

### Agent Mapping

Jig's core agents map to Codex as instruction files to be read and followed:

| Jig Agent | Path | Purpose |
|-----------|------|---------|
| `jig-commit` | `core/agents/commit.md` | Conventional commit workflow |
| `jig-code-review` | `core/agents/code-reviewer.md` | Review swarm dispatch |
| `jig-pr-review` | `core/agents/pr-reviewer.md` | Inline PR comment generation |

When a skill references an agent, read the agent's markdown file and execute
its instructions sequentially.

